※※
# codemod-sky-var

Manually-run workflow that bulk-renames ONE token across every `.sky` file in a
directory, consistently across its three syntactic forms, behind a manual gate, then
lints every touched file. Pure bash, no LLM tokens.

A `--var` key (or a node id) shows up in three places in a `.sky` file, and a rename
must hit all three or the workflow breaks:

  1. template form  {{old}}            (in ∆ prompt / http / eval bodies)
  2. bash env form  $SKY_<UPPER_OLD>   (UPPER_OLD = old uppercased, '-' -> '_')
  3. node-id form   §old§  and  ∆old∆  (the prompt body pairs to §old§ by id),
                    plus the quoted "old" refs in depends_on / chain_from

  (manual run: --var dir, old, new)
       │
       ▼
   ┌────────┐  compute UPPER forms; grep -n the three forms across <dir>/*.sky;
   │  scan  │  print every hit + the set of affected files. No hits ──▶ stop (exit 1).
   └────────┘
       │ hits found
       ▼
   ┌────────┐  ⏸ manual approval gate (timeout 1h)
   │  gate  │  shows the planned old -> new edit. Reject ──▶ stop, nothing changed.
   └────────┘
       │ approve
       ▼
   ┌────────┐  per affected file, portable temp-file sed rewrites all three forms:
   │ apply  │  {{old}}->{{new}}, $SKY_<UPPER_OLD>->$SKY_<UPPER_NEW>, §old§->§new§,
   └────────┘  ∆old∆->∆new∆, and the quoted "old" id refs in depends_on / chain_from.
       │
       ▼
   ┌────────┐  sky lint each touched file; exit 1 if ANY fails.
   │ verify │
   └────────┘

Run it (state the directory and the rename with --var):

  sky run codemod-sky-var \
    --var dir=".sky/workflows" \
    --var old="old-token" \
    --var new="new-token"

  - dir   directory of .sky files to codemod — STATE THIS (e.g. .sky/workflows)
  - old   the existing token (kebab-case --var key OR node id), WITHOUT $SKY_ / §
  - new   the replacement token (kebab-case), WITHOUT $SKY_ / §

HONEST WARNING — read before approving the gate. The three-form rewrite is plain
regex sed, so it is FRAGILE: a short or common `old` token (e.g. "x", "id", "run")
can false-match unrelated text — the quoted "old" rule rewrites ANY "old" string,
not only depends_on/chain_from values, and {{old}} / §old§ are matched literally.
That is exactly why this workflow (a) GATES every change behind manual approval so you
review the scan preview first, and (b) LINT-VERIFIES every touched file afterward.
Prefer long, distinctive tokens. The bash env form is word-boundary guarded so
$SKY_OLD does not clobber $SKY_OLD_EXTRA, but the other two forms are not — review the
scan output carefully. Use a git working tree so you can `git diff` / revert.
※※

⊕meta⊕
name = "codemod-sky-var"
description = "Bulk-rename one token across every .sky in a dir, consistently across its three forms ({{old}}, $SKY_<UPPER_OLD>, §old§ + quoted id refs), behind a manual gate, then lint every touched file. Pure bash, fragile regex so gated + verified. Fire via: sky run codemod-sky-var --var dir=<dir> --var old=<token> --var new=<token>"
trigger.manual = true
output_style = "terse"
⊕⊕

※scan※
Step 1 — scan. Computes the uppercase env-var forms of old/new, then greps every
.sky in the dir for the three forms and prints a numbered preview of each hit plus
the set of affected files. Hard-fails (exit 1) on a missing dir, a missing token,
or zero hits — there is nothing to codemod and nothing to approve in those cases.
※※

※scan※
Greps all three token forms across dir/*.sky; prints hits + affected file list; exits 1 on missing dir, missing token, or zero hits. No dependencies.
※※
§scan§
bash_file = "./scripts/scan.sh"
§§

※gate※
Step 2 — gate. Manual approval before any edit. The rewrite is regex-fragile (see the
header), so a human reviews the scan preview and approves. Reject to stop with nothing
changed; auto-stops after 1h if nobody answers. depends_on: scan.
※※

※gate※
Manual approval before any edit; shows scan preview; rejects stop workflow with nothing changed; timeout 1h. depends_on=["scan"].
※※
§gate§
depends_on = ["scan"]
wait.prompt = "Rewrite all three forms of '{{old}}' -> '{{new}}' across the affected .sky files in {{dir}}? Review the scan preview first — short/common tokens can false-match. Approve to apply."
wait.channel = "manual"
wait.timeout = "1h"
§§

※apply※
Step 3 — apply. For each affected file, a portable temp-file sed (no `sed -i`, macOS +
Linux safe) rewrites the three forms in order: template {{old}}->{{new}}, bash env
$SKY_<UPPER_OLD>->$SKY_<UPPER_NEW> (word-boundary guarded so $SKY_OLD_EXTRA is spared),
node-id §old§->§new§ and the matching prompt-block opener ∆old∆->∆new∆, then the
quoted "old"->"new" id refs used in depends_on / chain_from. Only files that contain
a form are touched. depends_on: gate.
※※

※apply※
Portable temp-file sed rewrites all three token forms per affected file; only touches files with a match. depends_on=["gate"].
※※
§apply§
depends_on = ["gate"]
bash_file = "./scripts/apply.sh"
§§

※verify※
Step 4 — verify. Pure-bash gate: re-lints every .sky in the dir (a touched file with
a broken reference is the failure we care about) and exits non-zero if any fails, so
a bad codemod surfaces immediately. The fragile rewrite is only trusted once this
passes — review `git diff` regardless. depends_on: apply.
※※

※verify※
Re-lints every .sky in dir; exits nonzero if any fails (surfacing a bad codemod). depends_on=["apply"].
※※
§verify§
depends_on = ["apply"]
bash_file = "./scripts/verify.sh"
§§
